2026-03-30 14:58:41 - Agent_20260330145159 - INFO - [+] Agent signaled completion: Reviewed 10 CodeQL queries covering XStream deserialization vulnerabilities across 12 specific locations. All findings were confirmed as true positives (critical severity). The vulnerabilities span the core XStream deserialization infrastructure:

1. DynamicProxyConverter (line 124/131) - Creates Java dynamic proxies with XML-controlled interface types and handler classes (CVE-2021-21346/21349 pattern)
2. CGLIBEnhancedConverter (line 344) - Creates CGLIB proxies from XML-controlled class names (CVE-2021-21344/21345 pattern)
3. XStreamer (line 271/275) - Double-deserialization: first deserializes attacker-controlled XStream config, then uses it to deserialize arbitrary objects
4. PureJavaReflectionProvider (line 136) - Uses ObjectInputStream.readObject() to instantiate XML-controlled types, triggering their deserialization lifecycle methods
5. ExternalizableConverter (line 192) - Calls readExternal() on XML-controlled Externalizable objects
6. SubjectConverter (line 84) - Instantiates arbitrary classes as principals/credentials from XML (CVE-2021-21347 pattern)
7. AbstractReflectionConverter (line 342/565) - Core class resolution and instantiation from XML-controlled names including 'resolves-to' attribute
8. SerializableConverter (line 462/464) - Resolves XML-controlled class names and invokes their readObject() methods
9. SerializationMembers (line 74/97/126/146) - Reflectively invokes readResolve/readObject/writeReplace/writeObject on XML-controlled objects
10. JavaMethodConverter (line 141/143) - getDeclaredMethod/getDeclaredConstructor with XML-controlled class and method names
11. AnnotationMapper (line 521) - readObject() during XStream config deserialization
12. PackageAliasingMapper (line 100) - readObject() during XStream config deserialization

All findings represent serious unsafe deserialization vulnerabilities in XStream's core infrastructure with no effective mitigations at the converter level (type permission checks in SecurityMapper can be bypassed or misconfigured by users).
